The article announces new commitments and programs in Liberia as part of the Let Girls Learn initiative. The U.S. Government, through USAID and the Peace Corps, is dedicating up to $27 million in funding to support Let Girls Learn. The new programs aim to address the barriers that prevent girls from attaining an education. They include initiatives to increase enrollment and safe access to education, provide support for out-of-school girls and youth, and support the education of girls with disabilities. The Peace Corps is expanding its Let Girls Learn program in Liberia with new volunteers working in the education sector. The article also highlights ongoing initiatives by USAID, the U.S. Department of Labor, and the U.S. Department of Agriculture to reduce barriers to adolescent girls' education in Liberia.